Description of male ( MIN 12 _ AMP 9 , Davao Oriental). Head: Labium mostly pale. Mandible bases and genae shining dark brown. Labrum, clypeus, frons and vertex to level of lateral ocelli black with metallic green reflection, remainder of dorsum of head matte black with indistinct brown areas on protruding postocular lobes, joined by brown band (
Fig. 15
); underside extensively pale. Antennae dark brown and black.

Thorax: Pronotum and propleuron largely black, pair of pale marks on anterior pronotal lobe, brown marks on rear of middle pronotal lobe, small pale marks laterally on posterior pronotal lobe. Dorsum of synthorax matte black with small pale mark between arms of anterior bifurcation of middorsal carina. Synthorax laterally with bright pale marks as follows (
Fig. 21
): along lower side of mesopleural suture a long streak and short streak near antealar carina, longer streak running almost whole length of interpleural suture, narrowly interrupted at ca half its length, larger light brown area above interpleural suture between coxae, larger subtriangular area under metapleural suture near antealar carina, short pale streak under metapleural suture joined to indistinct pale brownish marking adjacent to metinfraepisternum. Area between metapleural carina and venter dark brown. Venter of synthorax brown and pale (
Fig. 30
). Legs: Coxae and trochanters brown. Femora extensor surface brown, flexor surface obscurely brown and grey. Tibiae and tarsi dark brown. Wings with arculus ca level of Ax 5 , quadrilateral with 2 crossveins, cubito-anal space free in all wings, pt brown with paler center. Wing membrane with faint brownish tint, tips of both wings with heavier brown colour.

Abdomen: Very dark brown to black, S 3–7 with broad pale basal ring, brown dorsally, faint lateral remnant of this on S 8 . Genital ligula typical for the group, seminal vesicle light brown. Anal appendages black. Paraprocts extremely short, rounded, black. Cerci longer than S 10 , in dorsal view (
Fig. 41
) abruptly curved inward after mid length, apical part at more than right angle to proximal part, left cercus lying over right. In both dorsal and lateral (
Fig. 47
) views widest at base, narrowing toward turn then moderately expanded apically. Interior surface with slotlike excavation around middle part, extending towards apex, brownish inside groove.

Description of female (Mt Makatoring, North Cotabato). As male except as noted. Head. Extensively brown, postocular lobes pale brown (
Fig. 53
). Antennae with scape largely pale.

Thorax: Pronotum (
Fig. 59
) mottled brown, pale marks on anterior lobe, posterior lobe with yellow lateral patches, extensive whitish grey pruinosity on propleuron. No horns on the middle pronotal lobe. Dorsum of synthorax brown with middorsal carina black, bluish pale mark between arms of anterior bifurcation of middorsal carina. Synthorax laterally brown with pale marks as in male, but pale band under interpleural suture not interrupted (
Fig. 69
). Patches of whitish grey pruinosity present, venter of synthorax covered with this. Legs with pruinosity on coxae, Wings with arculus at Ax 5 in all wings, quadrilateral with three crossveins in right Fw, pt black proximally apical ca one-half mostly whitish. Extreme tips of both wings heavily tinted brown, a little darker in Hw.
